			<description><![CDATA[I've posted about this a few times before. Every now and then EA gives away a free classic game as a way to get people to try their Origin service. It's basically advertising, as when you log in to download your free game you also happen to see their banners proclaiming whatever new release they...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I've posted about this a few times before. Every now and then EA gives away a free classic game as a way to get people to try their Origin service. It's basically advertising, as when you log in to download your free game you also happen to see their banners proclaiming whatever new release they have coming up is available for pre-order.<br />
<br />
At any rate, if you like RTS games and never tried it, or already own it physical and would like a digital version, Red Alert 2 along with it's expansion are free at the moment. There was a brief issue where demand was too high and they ran out of keys, but it's available again now.<br />
<br />
<br />
